For the provided scientific data, the following additions apply:
The COVID19 data files may be used or distributed and reformatted, ammended, analysed etc. in any way possible.
The data files may however NOT be presented, released, reported about or even modified in any way that would have potential for causing major scientific confusion about the contents within.

Any copy of the data files shall include the source of the files.
For the tsv-originals: The original source (impfdashboard.de) must be listed.
(The detailed source urls for the original files are to be taken from the document titled "README.md".)

Any modifications must be clearly stated and explained in enough detail along with every copy.
It must be written, at least additionally, in proper English language, to aide international comprehensibility.

[Recommendation]
A file or database format outside of standardized data file formats* is discouraged BUT ALLOED nonetheless IF at minimum a link to the data format specification is clearly provided.
At best, you would include the full format specification with the project itself, provided the docs license provides that ability, legally speaking. 
(If your file format is not in the list below, be readay to provide a publicly accessible specification of the file format. Alternatively, if for whatever reason you can only provide a link that is accessible to the people you are sharing the data with, that will also be fine.)

*Some examples of standardized file formats (no intention for being exhaustive):
json, tsv, csv, xml, sqlite, xls/xlsx


